WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.600 --> 00:00:20.019
7-Adam-15. we're code 6
at the 911 call location.

2
00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.729
Any further contact from
the distressed individual?

3
00:00:21.730 --> 00:00:23.064
<i>Negative.</i>

4
00:00:23.065 --> 00:00:24.607
<i>Do you want me to start
additional units?</i>

5
00:00:24.608 --> 00:00:27.401
Uh. no. Give us a minute
to scope it out first.

6
00:00:27.402 --> 00:00:29.529
You ready?
- Do I have a choice?

7
00:00:29.530 --> 00:00:30.822
That's the spirit.

8
00:00:38.205 --> 00:00:39.664
LAPD.

9
00:00:39.665 --> 00:00:41.624
We've received a distress call
from this location.

10
00:00:41.625 --> 00:00:44.210
We are making entry.

11
00:00:46.213 --> 00:00:47.713
Ooh.

12
00:00:51.051 --> 00:00:53.427
Oh.
Do you feel that?

13
00:00:53.428 --> 00:00:54.428
Feel what?

14
00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:56.597
Ah. something evil's in here.

15
00:00:56.598 --> 00:00:58.392
Well. sure smells like it.

16
00:01:06.024 --> 00:01:09.652
<i>I can't die.</i>

17
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:14.115
<i>Won't let me die.</i>

18
00:01:14.116 --> 00:01:16.576
- Police.
Show yourself.

19
00:01:19.121 --> 00:01:21.706
- I can't die.
It's inside of me.

20
00:01:21.707 --> 00:01:24.083
It won't let me die.
- Don't touch that. all right?

21
00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:25.751
Just... call this in.
Call it in.

22
00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:28.004
I need an RA to my location
for a stabbing victim.

23
00:01:28.005 --> 00:01:29.588
So I usually sit
right next to camera

24
00:01:29.589 --> 00:01:30.840
to keep the eyeline tight.

25
00:01:30.841 --> 00:01:32.508
Then I'll just sit
on the other side.

26
00:01:32.509 --> 00:01:33.843
No. because then
you'll split his look.

27
00:01:33.844 --> 00:01:35.845
- I don't think it matters.
- Oh. hey. Hi.

28
00:01:35.846 --> 00:01:37.680
Thanks... thanks again
for sitting down with me.

29
00:01:37.681 --> 00:01:40.308
- Us.
- What? Oh. right. us.

30
00:01:40.309 --> 00:01:42.476
Uh. why are you filming?

31
00:01:42.477 --> 00:01:44.145
Oh. I just wanted to document
the new partnership.

32
00:01:44.146 --> 00:01:45.813
Abigail was very excited.

33
00:01:45.814 --> 00:01:47.690
- It's not a partnership.
- It's totally a partnership.

34
00:01:47.691 --> 00:01:49.900
The judge was very clear.
- The judge?

35
00:01:49.901 --> 00:01:51.277
My name is Abigail Tierney.

36
00:01:51.278 --> 00:01:53.321
I'm currently trapped
inside a secret lab

37
00:01:53.322 --> 00:01:54.697
at Westview Psychiatric.

38
00:01:54.698 --> 00:01:57.283
All attempts at escape
have proven fruitless.

39
00:01:57.284 --> 00:01:59.618
I may have inadvertently used
some of Abigail's footage

40
00:01:59.619 --> 00:02:02.580
in my last documentary without
gaining the proper permissions.

41
00:02:02.581 --> 00:02:05.791
Translation. he stole
my intellectual property.

42
00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:08.251
I sued. and the judge
gave him a choice...

43
00:02:08.252 --> 00:02:10.338
pay me 200 thou in damages
or give me equal partnership

44
00:02:10.339 --> 00:02:11.797
in his next project.

45
00:02:11.798 --> 00:02:13.215
He never said equal.
but you know what?

46
00:02:13.216 --> 00:02:14.925
Never mind.

47
00:02:14.926 --> 00:02:16.761
Let's focus on the story
that we're here to tell.

48
00:02:16.762 --> 00:02:18.055
Have a seat.

49
00:02:19.473 --> 00:02:21.849
Perhaps the most shocking
case of murder

50
00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:23.434
and mayhem we've ever seen.

51
00:02:23.435 --> 00:02:24.810
Would you say
that's a fair assessment?

52
00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:26.646
Um...

53
00:02:26.647 --> 00:02:28.272
- No. no. stay... stay back.
Stay back. Stay back.

54
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:29.607
You don't understand.
- OK. relax.

55
00:02:29.608 --> 00:02:31.942
OK. we're trying to help you.
Who stabbed you?

56
00:02:31.943 --> 00:02:33.944
I stabbed myself.

57
00:02:33.945 --> 00:02:36.697
It's inside of me.
I've tried everything else.

58
00:02:36.698 --> 00:02:37.907
I can't kill it.

59
00:02:37.908 --> 00:02:40.534
I can't die.
See?

60
00:02:40.535 --> 00:02:42.119
- No. don't pull that...
don't pull it out!

61
00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:43.413
Oh. God.

62
00:02:45.832 --> 00:02:47.083
Oh. he died instantly.

63
00:02:47.084 --> 00:02:49.502
I mean. the wound was fatal.

64
00:02:49.503 --> 00:02:52.380
You can't stab yourself
in the heart and survive.

65
00:02:52.381 --> 00:02:55.591
But the way the knife
was lodged.

66
00:02:55.592 --> 00:02:56.675
he wasn't bleeding.

67
00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:58.427
Once he pulled it out...

68
00:02:58.428 --> 00:03:01.055
- It was blood fountain city.
- Not exactly. but...

69
00:03:01.056 --> 00:03:03.265
As shocking as that was.
it was far from

70
00:03:03.266 --> 00:03:04.892
the most shocking thing
you found.

71
00:03:04.893 --> 00:03:06.227
Oh. we should get him
to say that

72
00:03:06.228 --> 00:03:07.728
to set up the opening credits.

73
00:03:07.729 --> 00:03:09.480
- That's not... we...
we don't put words

74
00:03:09.481 --> 00:03:11.233
in people's mouths.
It's a documentary.

75
00:03:13.652 --> 00:03:16.821
Yeah. it was. uh.
straight-up crazy.

76
00:03:18.198 --> 00:03:20.074
- You don't think...
- There's a body in there.

77
00:03:21.827 --> 00:03:23.035
May have finally found it.

78
00:03:24.955 --> 00:03:26.288
Please don't kill us.

79
00:03:26.289 --> 00:03:27.998
We will join your cult.

80
00:03:27.999 --> 00:03:29.750
- Oh.
- Oh. God.

81
00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:32.128
You arrived on scene
as the sergeant's supervisor?

82
00:03:32.129 --> 00:03:33.421
Yes.

83
00:03:33.422 --> 00:03:35.548
I got there before
the ambulance.

84
00:03:35.549 --> 00:03:37.425
not that there was any aid
they could have rendered.

85
00:03:37.426 --> 00:03:38.968
Is there a reason
you didn't want us

86
00:03:38.969 --> 00:03:40.469
to interview you with Tim?

87
00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:41.637
What?

88
00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:43.222
No. We're just...

89
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:45.057
just shaking it up.

90
00:03:45.058 --> 00:03:46.434
- Let's... let's...
let's stay focused.

91
00:03:46.435 --> 00:03:48.227
Were you the first
to recognize the victim?

92
00:03:48.228 --> 00:03:50.354
Uh. sort of.

93
00:03:50.355 --> 00:03:53.232
I thought I knew his face.
but it wasn't until

94
00:03:53.233 --> 00:03:54.525
we ran his prints
that we got a name.

95
00:03:54.526 --> 00:03:57.486
Rich Rowley was retired LAPD.

96
00:03:57.487 --> 00:03:59.447
He had been with
the department for 30 years

97
00:03:59.448 --> 00:04:01.031
and was a little bit
of a legend.

98
00:04:01.032 --> 00:04:04.326
mostly because he made a series
of training videos

99
00:04:04.327 --> 00:04:07.913
from the mid-'90s
till his retirement in 2015.

100
00:04:07.914 --> 00:04:11.876
which by modern standards.
are a little cringe.

101
00:04:11.877 --> 00:04:13.794
- Hey. everybody.
Rich Rowley here

102
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:15.921
with another installment of...

103
00:04:18.007 --> 00:04:20.259
Now. today. we're gonna
be talking about

104
00:04:20.260 --> 00:04:22.928
proper cuffing technique.

105
00:04:22.929 --> 00:04:24.054
Excuse me. officer?

106
00:04:24.055 --> 00:04:26.307
I hurt my shoulder at the gym.

107
00:04:26.308 --> 00:04:28.185
Would you mind
cuffing me in front?

108
00:04:29.603 --> 00:04:32.646
Pretty lady like you.

109
00:04:32.647 --> 00:04:34.732
what's the worst
that could happen?

110
00:04:36.568 --> 00:04:39.445
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

111
00:04:41.865 --> 00:04:43.365
Rich was a trip.

112
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:46.368
The life of the party.
at least early in his career.

113
00:04:46.369 --> 00:04:48.120
Then as the years went on.

114
00:04:48.121 --> 00:04:51.832
he became a little. uh. crazy.

115
00:04:51.833 --> 00:04:53.250
Crazy how?

116
00:04:53.251 --> 00:04:55.169
He was deep into
conspiracy theories.

117
00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:58.839
He had a real thing
for cults and cabals.

118
00:04:58.840 --> 00:05:01.217
To be fair. Los Angeles does
have a pretty dark history.

119
00:05:01.218 --> 00:05:03.803
But Rich took it
to the next level.

120
00:05:03.804 --> 00:05:05.221
and his training videos got more

121
00:05:05.222 --> 00:05:06.639
and more intense because of it.

122
00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:08.349
We finally got around
to updating the videos

123
00:05:08.350 --> 00:05:11.268
this last year. but that
caused quite a controversy

124
00:05:11.269 --> 00:05:12.686
with some of the older officers.

125
00:05:12.687 --> 00:05:15.064
They said we were
being insensitive.

126
00:05:15.065 --> 00:05:17.650
Why would updating training
videos be insensitive?

127
00:05:17.651 --> 00:05:20.194
Even three years on.
a lot of his friends

128
00:05:20.195 --> 00:05:22.613
were still mourning his death
and saw the videos as a way

129
00:05:22.614 --> 00:05:24.990
to keep his memory alive.
- I'm sorry.

130
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:26.283
I thought Rich died
six months ago.

131
00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:28.285
- Yeah.
- He did.

132
00:05:28.286 --> 00:05:29.703
I'm talking about
the first time.

133
00:05:29.704 --> 00:05:31.455
<i>Divers are searching for</i>

134
00:05:31.456 --> 00:05:32.998
<i>any signs of retired</i>

135
00:05:32.999 --> 00:05:36.001
<i>Los Angeles police officer
Richard Rowley</i>

136
00:05:36.002 --> 00:05:37.920
<i>after a sailing trip gone wrong.</i>

137
00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:40.422
<i>Coast Guard responded
to a distress call</i>

138
00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:42.383
<i>this morning from Rowley's wife.</i>

139
00:05:42.384 --> 00:05:44.677
<i>who says the 55-year-old
fell overboard</i>

140
00:05:44.678 --> 00:05:46.679
<i>after the sailboat
he was captaining</i>

141
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:49.640
<i>was struck by a rogue wave.</i>

142
00:05:49.641 --> 00:05:51.809
Any time someone disappears
from a boating trip.

143
00:05:51.810 --> 00:05:53.352
it automatically sets off
alarm bells.

144
00:05:53.353 --> 00:05:54.979
Why is that?

145
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:56.814
It's just an ideal place
to cover up a crime.

146
00:05:56.815 --> 00:05:58.566
Throw a body overboard.
weigh it down.

147
00:05:58.567 --> 00:06:00.442
the likelihood of us
recovering it before

148
00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:02.486
it becomes fish food is low.

149
00:06:02.487 --> 00:06:05.155
And circumstances
were suspicious.

150
00:06:05.156 --> 00:06:07.491
By all accounts.
Rich was a skilled sailor.

151
00:06:07.492 --> 00:06:09.952
it was a calm day. and the
only witness to his demise

152
00:06:09.953 --> 00:06:13.163
was Darla Phillips.
his on again. off again

153
00:06:13.164 --> 00:06:15.207
girlfriend. who he married
five days prior.

154
00:06:15.208 --> 00:06:16.875
So you suspected foul play?

155
00:06:19.588 --> 00:06:21.922
Not necessarily.
but we couldn't rule it out.

156
00:06:21.923 --> 00:06:23.674
Why wasn't Rich
wearing a life vest?

157
00:06:23.675 --> 00:06:26.885
- He never did.
He was a strong swimmer.

158
00:06:26.886 --> 00:06:29.138
He must have hit
his head when he fell.

159
00:06:29.139 --> 00:06:30.890
Why didn't you
jump in after him?

160
00:06:30.891 --> 00:06:33.434
- I'm scared of dark water.
- Dark water?

161
00:06:33.435 --> 00:06:35.894
Water you can't see
the bottom of.

162
00:06:35.895 --> 00:06:37.980
Just blackness

163
00:06:37.981 --> 00:06:40.316
with God knows what
lurking below.

164
00:06:40.317 --> 00:06:42.902
You stand to inherit
Rich's entire police pension.

165
00:06:42.903 --> 00:06:44.320
That's quite a bit of money.

166
00:06:44.321 --> 00:06:46.238
How dare you?

167
00:06:46.239 --> 00:06:50.618
I just watched the love of
my life die in front of me.

168
00:06:50.619 --> 00:06:52.536
We don't know that for sure yet.

169
00:06:52.537 --> 00:06:54.663
They haven't found his body.

170
00:06:54.664 --> 00:06:58.792
Unless you know more
that you're not telling us.

171
00:06:58.793 --> 00:07:00.544
Go to hell!

172
00:07:00.545 --> 00:07:02.254
This interview is over.

173
00:07:02.255 --> 00:07:04.757
Did it ever occur to you
that Rich might still be alive?

174
00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:06.675
As we said. we couldn't
rule anything out.

175
00:07:06.676 --> 00:07:10.220
but there was no evidence
that he'd faked his death.

176
00:07:10.221 --> 00:07:11.847
Until he turned up dead again.

177
00:07:11.848 --> 00:07:14.433
Needless to say. we had
a few more questions for Darla.

178
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:16.810
Helping someone fake
their death isn't a crime.

179
00:07:16.811 --> 00:07:18.228
I checked.
- You're right.

180
00:07:18.229 --> 00:07:20.022
but profiting off of that death.

181
00:07:20.023 --> 00:07:21.857
collecting Rich's pension
and his life insurance.

182
00:07:21.858 --> 00:07:23.817
that's fraud.

183
00:07:23.818 --> 00:07:26.111
Not to mention the resources
that were wasted

184
00:07:26.112 --> 00:07:27.363
trying to recover his body.

185
00:07:27.364 --> 00:07:29.907
You could be facing
some serious charges.

186
00:07:29.908 --> 00:07:32.159
So tell us.

187
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:34.079
Why did Rich want to
fake his death?

188
00:07:35.413 --> 00:07:39.333
After Rich retired.
he kind of fell apart.

189
00:07:39.334 --> 00:07:43.253
His drinking got worse.
and his paranoia.

190
00:07:43.254 --> 00:07:45.756
He was always a little intense.

191
00:07:45.757 --> 00:07:48.217
but it started to get scary.

192
00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:51.553
He covered all his windows
with newspapers.

193
00:07:51.554 --> 00:07:55.224
started writing down the
license plates of passing cars.

194
00:07:55.225 --> 00:07:57.142
What was he so afraid of?

195
00:07:57.143 --> 00:07:59.895
He said there was
this group. like.

196
00:07:59.896 --> 00:08:05.067
a secret society of dangerous
and powerful people.

197
00:08:05.068 --> 00:08:06.944
He'd been on to them for years.

198
00:08:06.945 --> 00:08:08.737
He said that they found out
about him.

199
00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:10.906
that he was in danger
because of it.

200
00:08:10.907 --> 00:08:13.867
It was too much for me.
so I broke up with him.

201
00:08:13.868 --> 00:08:17.871
And then a year later.
he showed up on my doorstep

202
00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:21.000
and asked me to help him
fake his death

203
00:08:21.001 --> 00:08:23.585
in return for his pension.

204
00:08:23.586 --> 00:08:25.087
I needed the money.

205
00:08:25.088 --> 00:08:27.965
So we got married.
and we did the deed.

206
00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:29.925
and I never saw him again.

207
00:08:29.926 --> 00:08:33.846
So you have no idea why there
was a coffin in his garage?

208
00:08:33.847 --> 00:08:35.346
We'll probably hold
this piece of the puzzle

209
00:08:35.347 --> 00:08:37.099
until the end of the first act.
you know.

210
00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.307
hit the audience
with a twist when

211
00:08:38.308 --> 00:08:40.310
it's dramatically expedient.
- Yeah.

212
00:08:40.311 --> 00:08:41.478
Seems manipulative.

213
00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:42.980
All good storytelling is. so.

214
00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:45.607
Just tell us about
finding the coffin.

215
00:08:45.608 --> 00:08:49.486
So once I arrived.
and we secured the crime scene.

216
00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:51.280
we cleared
the rest of the house.

217
00:08:51.281 --> 00:08:52.115
and then we moved on
to the garage.

218
00:08:56.619 --> 00:08:57.619
Oh.

219
00:08:57.620 --> 00:08:59.538
Oh. you don't think there's...

220
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:02.833
- That there's a body in there?
I absolutely do.

221
00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:06.462
- OK. are we gonna open it?
'Cause I don't wanna open it.

222
00:09:06.463 --> 00:09:07.921
What do you think?

223
00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:10.299
I mean.
it's clearly been dug up.

224
00:09:10.300 --> 00:09:12.468
Given the state of the coffin.
it's clearly been

225
00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:13.927
underground for a few years.

226
00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:16.680
If there is a body in there.
it's likely long dead.

227
00:09:16.681 --> 00:09:19.308
- Unless...
- Unless what?

228
00:09:19.309 --> 00:09:22.269
Unless he put a fresh victim
in an old coffin.

229
00:09:24.731 --> 00:09:26.648
OK. got it.

230
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:28.067
- Got it?
- Yep.

231
00:09:28.068 --> 00:09:30.235
- Oh.
Oh. God.

232
00:09:37.494 --> 00:09:38.911
The body belonged to
a 54-year-old truck driver

233
00:09:38.912 --> 00:09:40.913
named Marcus Ford.

234
00:09:40.914 --> 00:09:42.748
<i>who was the victim of
an unsolved homicide</i>

235
00:09:42.749 --> 00:09:44.333
<i>back in 2020.</i>

236
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:45.375
How was he killed?

237
00:09:45.376 --> 00:09:47.377
Uh. he was stabbed in the heart.

238
00:09:47.378 --> 00:09:49.546
Just like Rich.

239
00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:52.174
Wait. Rich murdered Marcus Ford.

240
00:09:52.175 --> 00:09:54.134
Did I just solve the case?
- No.

241
00:09:54.135 --> 00:09:58.013
We were able to alibi Rich out.

242
00:09:58.014 --> 00:10:00.265
He was hospitalized with double
pneumonia the day Marcus died.

243
00:10:00.266 --> 00:10:02.476
Medical records say
he was so weak that.

244
00:10:02.477 --> 00:10:04.144
uh. he could barely
get out of bed.

245
00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:05.687
Or that's what
he wanted you to think.

246
00:10:05.688 --> 00:10:06.980
Moving on.

247
00:10:06.981 --> 00:10:08.357
Digging up a body's
no easy task.

248
00:10:08.358 --> 00:10:10.067
Why would Rich go
to all that trouble?

249
00:10:10.068 --> 00:10:12.402
Initially.
we thought it was simply

250
00:10:12.403 --> 00:10:15.823
the demented act of
a clearly disturbed mind.

251
00:10:15.824 --> 00:10:17.658
and in some ways. it was.

252
00:10:17.659 --> 00:10:20.160
But then we found the tattoo.

253
00:10:20.161 --> 00:10:21.995
At first. it was
a little bit difficult

254
00:10:21.996 --> 00:10:23.914
to make out exactly what it was.

255
00:10:23.915 --> 00:10:27.334
A half a decade of decomp
does a number on the skin.

256
00:10:27.335 --> 00:10:29.920
But when we look back
at the case file.

257
00:10:29.921 --> 00:10:32.297
there was a photo of it taken
during the original autopsy.

258
00:10:32.298 --> 00:10:33.674
That's actually kind of sick.

259
00:10:33.675 --> 00:10:35.801
I wonder if there's a way
to track down the artist.

260
00:10:35.802 --> 00:10:36.969
I've been meaning
to start the sleeve

261
00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:38.846
on my other arm. like a...

262
00:10:38.847 --> 00:10:40.347
To my collaborator's point.

263
00:10:40.348 --> 00:10:42.432
lots of people have tattoos.

264
00:10:42.433 --> 00:10:44.726
What was it about this one
that jumped out at you?

265
00:10:44.727 --> 00:10:47.980
Well. something about it
was familiar to both of us.

266
00:10:47.981 --> 00:10:49.815
but we couldn't place it.

267
00:10:49.816 --> 00:10:53.277
So we started asking around.
and the answer couldn't come

268
00:10:53.278 --> 00:10:56.196
from a more unlikely place.

269
00:10:56.197 --> 00:10:58.073
I watched the Rich Rowley
training videos

270
00:10:58.074 --> 00:11:00.534
more than any person alive.

271
00:11:00.535 --> 00:11:04.079
so I recognized
the symbol immediately.

272
00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:06.290
Sometimes. citizens panic when

273
00:11:06.291 --> 00:11:08.959
they can't get in touch with
their friends or loved ones.

274
00:11:08.960 --> 00:11:11.003
That is why we always
advise the public

275
00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:14.423
to wait 24 hours before
reporting someone missing.

276
00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:16.383
While most missing
person reports stem

277
00:11:16.384 --> 00:11:18.093
from a lapse in communication.

278
00:11:18.094 --> 00:11:19.970
every once in a while.
you'll encounter

279
00:11:19.971 --> 00:11:22.556
a true. workable case.

280
00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:25.350
- Officer. help.
My sister is missing.

281
00:11:25.351 --> 00:11:26.810
When's the last time
you saw her?

282
00:11:26.811 --> 00:11:28.478
Last night at the bar.

283
00:11:28.479 --> 00:11:30.856
Her boyfriend said
she never made it home.

284
00:11:30.857 --> 00:11:34.693
You always wanna take a
report like this one seriously.

285
00:11:34.694 --> 00:11:37.279
<i>So Rich hid the same symbol
in his training videos</i>

286
00:11:37.280 --> 00:11:39.656
<i>that was tattooed on
the body of a murder victim.</i>

287
00:11:39.657 --> 00:11:41.867
What did you think that meant?

288
00:11:41.868 --> 00:11:44.119
Uh. I don't know.

289
00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:44.870
I can't believe I'm saying this.

290
00:11:44.871 --> 00:11:46.079
but Smitty was right.

291
00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:48.081
In lesson 187. the tattoo symbol

292
00:11:48.082 --> 00:11:49.958
was hidden in the background.

293
00:11:49.959 --> 00:11:51.668
although the instructions

294
00:11:51.669 --> 00:11:53.962
to wait 24 hours before
reporting a missing person

295
00:11:53.963 --> 00:11:55.881
are wildly outdated.

296
00:11:55.882 --> 00:11:57.633
Anyways. it got me thinking.

297
00:11:57.634 --> 00:12:00.802
What if Rich put messages
in other videos?

298
00:12:00.803 --> 00:12:02.054
What kind of messages?

299
00:12:02.055 --> 00:12:03.513
I'm not totally sure yet.

300
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:05.557
I binged every single
Rich training video

301
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:06.558
I could get my hands on.

302
00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:08.101
Yeah. it's been
a fun few nights.

303
00:12:08.102 --> 00:12:10.020
And I did find a few
other possible leads.

304
00:12:10.021 --> 00:12:11.355
but there's a problem.

305
00:12:11.356 --> 00:12:12.648
The department's
archive is incomplete.

306
00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:14.066
and without all of the videos.

307
00:12:14.067 --> 00:12:15.233
I can't be sure
that I'm not missing

308
00:12:15.234 --> 00:12:16.652
a vital piece of information.

309
00:12:16.653 --> 00:12:18.528
So what happened
to the missing videos?

310
00:12:18.529 --> 00:12:20.697
So when the training topics
and the videos

311
00:12:20.698 --> 00:12:24.326
become outdated because
of new laws or protocols.

312
00:12:24.327 --> 00:12:26.036
the department has
to make new ones.

313
00:12:26.037 --> 00:12:28.497
and obsolete videos
are supposed to be digitized

314
00:12:28.498 --> 00:12:31.708
and archived
for historical record.

315
00:12:31.709 --> 00:12:34.086
But Rich's were just gone.

316
00:12:34.087 --> 00:12:35.712
Gone as in destroyed?

317
00:12:35.713 --> 00:12:38.340
- Like a cover-up?
- No one's saying that.

318
00:12:38.341 --> 00:12:40.550
Most likely.
it was a human error.

319
00:12:40.551 --> 00:12:43.178
You know. someone got lazy.
didn't archive them.

320
00:12:43.179 --> 00:12:45.013
I tried reaching out
to the production company

321
00:12:45.014 --> 00:12:48.183
that made the videos to see
if they had any copies left.

322
00:12:48.184 --> 00:12:51.228
Bad news is they went out
of business a few years back

323
00:12:51.229 --> 00:12:53.105
and auctioned off
all their equipment.

324
00:12:53.106 --> 00:12:55.190
What's the good news?

325
00:12:55.191 --> 00:12:58.485
Well. I managed to track down
the auction logs.

326
00:12:58.486 --> 00:13:00.487
and I actually know
the person who purchased

327
00:13:00.488 --> 00:13:02.948
the studio's old hard drives.

328
00:13:02.949 --> 00:13:06.201
Careful. I'm very ticklish.
like the Pillsbury Doughboy.

329
00:13:06.202 --> 00:13:07.202
Same.

330
00:13:07.203 --> 00:13:09.246
I hear it's a sign
of intelligence.

331
00:13:09.247 --> 00:13:10.539
- Is that a fact?
- Yep.

332
00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:13.166
Then I am smart as the dickens.

333
00:13:13.167 --> 00:13:14.918
So you purchased hard drives

334
00:13:14.919 --> 00:13:16.753
from Speak Now Studios?

335
00:13:16.754 --> 00:13:18.839
Yeah. Dropout was still
in its infancy.

336
00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:21.133
I was building the company
from the ground up.

337
00:13:21.134 --> 00:13:23.385
We had to be smart about
how we were spending our money.

338
00:13:23.386 --> 00:13:26.054
We bought a huge amount
of equipment secondhand...

339
00:13:26.055 --> 00:13:27.973
hard drives. cameras. wigs.

340
00:13:27.974 --> 00:13:31.018
Wait. you bought
second-hand wigs?

341
00:13:31.019 --> 00:13:32.310
Give them a little shake
before we put them on.

342
00:13:32.311 --> 00:13:33.770
That's awesome.

343
00:13:33.771 --> 00:13:35.022
Do you still have
that wig connect?

344
00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:37.649
'Cause I'd love a referral.
My guy is...

345
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.526
Back on track.

346
00:13:39.527 --> 00:13:41.778
The hard drives you bought
contain police training videos.

347
00:13:41.779 --> 00:13:43.363
Did you happen to watch
any of them?

348
00:13:43.364 --> 00:13:45.365
- Of course.
Rich Rowley. right?

349
00:13:45.366 --> 00:13:47.367
We were obsessed
with those videos.

350
00:13:47.368 --> 00:13:50.078
We probably watched them.
like. a dozen times.

351
00:13:50.079 --> 00:13:52.748
I'm Rich Rowley. and this is
"Survive the Streets."

352
00:13:52.749 --> 00:13:54.374
Oh. that's great.

353
00:13:54.375 --> 00:13:55.751
Vic can do the best impression.

354
00:13:55.752 --> 00:13:57.669
Do you think you'd be able
to make copies for us?

355
00:13:57.670 --> 00:14:00.047
I totally would.

356
00:14:00.048 --> 00:14:01.339
but I can't because

357
00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:03.050
we wiped all of those
hard drives

358
00:14:03.051 --> 00:14:04.634
to use as servers months ago.

359
00:14:04.635 --> 00:14:06.511
Sorry I couldn't be
of more help.

360
00:14:06.512 --> 00:14:10.348
You'll still feature
this interview. right?

361
00:14:10.349 --> 00:14:11.933
- Yeah.
- Yeah. probably not.

362
00:14:11.934 --> 00:14:13.727
Wait. you said you
and the Dropout crew

363
00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:16.480
watched the video. like.
dozens of times. right?

364
00:14:16.481 --> 00:14:18.607
Yes. sometimes on an edible.
mostly sober.

365
00:14:18.608 --> 00:14:20.525
I have an idea.

366
00:14:20.526 --> 00:14:21.985
OK. so then he'd be like.
don't forget to check

367
00:14:21.986 --> 00:14:23.487
the closet or you'll die.
So I don't know.

368
00:14:23.488 --> 00:14:25.197
I think it's
a little bit more like.

369
00:14:25.198 --> 00:14:26.990
like. if you forget
to check the closet.

370
00:14:26.991 --> 00:14:29.701
Freddy. Jason. and Chucky
will rip off your scrote!

371
00:14:29.702 --> 00:14:31.453
OK. I think
there's less foot stuff.

372
00:14:31.454 --> 00:14:33.038
I feel like he's like...

373
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:35.040
and then your crazy
methy ex-girlfriend

374
00:14:35.041 --> 00:14:37.250
who's been hiding in
the hallway closet

375
00:14:37.251 --> 00:14:39.127
will chainsaw your face
when you get home

376
00:14:39.128 --> 00:14:41.004
because you forgot
to clear the room!

377
00:14:41.005 --> 00:14:42.005
- Clear the room!
- Clear the room!

378
00:14:42.006 --> 00:14:43.590
Check the room.

379
00:14:43.591 --> 00:14:45.550
I think he was so close
to pulling out his gun...

380
00:14:45.551 --> 00:14:47.302
- What are you guys doing?
- That's a great question.

381
00:14:47.303 --> 00:14:48.929
They're reenacting
the police training videos

382
00:14:48.930 --> 00:14:50.263
since you guys wiped them
off your hard drive.

383
00:14:50.264 --> 00:14:51.932
Oh. the Rich Rowley ones.

384
00:14:51.933 --> 00:14:53.433
Those are so funny.
- Right.

385
00:14:53.434 --> 00:14:54.935
I actually stole
one of the hard drives

386
00:14:54.936 --> 00:14:56.144
so I could watch it
when I'm in the tub.

387
00:14:56.145 --> 00:14:57.312
You talking about
your tub again?

388
00:14:57.313 --> 00:14:58.480
- Say what?
- A little self-care.

389
00:14:58.481 --> 00:15:00.232
You know.
trying to relax a little more.

390
00:15:00.233 --> 00:15:02.317
It's not working.
- Can we have it?

391
00:15:02.318 --> 00:15:03.944
If you want to borrow it.
I could. you know.

392
00:15:03.945 --> 00:15:05.404
No. I think this is
actually working great.

393
00:15:05.405 --> 00:15:07.906
- I mean. you could. OK.
- Keep this up.

394
00:15:07.907 --> 00:15:08.782
- Riffing.
- Clearing the room.

395
00:15:08.783 --> 00:15:10.117
Help us.

396
00:15:10.118 --> 00:15:11.368
OK. I finally finished watching

397
00:15:11.369 --> 00:15:12.953
all of the Rich training videos.

398
00:15:12.954 --> 00:15:14.412
and there is a lot.

399
00:15:14.413 --> 00:15:17.499
Um. take lesson 277...

400
00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:22.504
My azaleas!

401
00:15:22.505 --> 00:15:26.133
A cold case where victim
Azalea Robinson was found

402
00:15:26.134 --> 00:15:27.968
stabbed near a ski resort.

403
00:15:27.969 --> 00:15:29.344
- You're kidding.
- No.

404
00:15:29.345 --> 00:15:32.347
And in lesson 290.
Rich is holding a folder

405
00:15:32.348 --> 00:15:34.141
with a Post-It note
on the back with a brown star

406
00:15:34.142 --> 00:15:35.475
drawn on it.
- I'm lost.

407
00:15:35.476 --> 00:15:38.228
Right. so I looked up
the cold cases

408
00:15:38.229 --> 00:15:39.938
to see if there were
any victims with names

409
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:41.857
like Star or Stella.

410
00:15:41.858 --> 00:15:43.358
and there was one hit.

411
00:15:43.359 --> 00:15:44.860
Stella Brown.

412
00:15:44.861 --> 00:15:47.154
also found stabbed in the chest.

413
00:15:47.155 --> 00:15:49.114
In all.
Lucy found clues pointing

414
00:15:49.115 --> 00:15:51.533
to seven different cold cases.

415
00:15:51.534 --> 00:15:53.535
But why was Rich hiding
the names of murder victims

416
00:15:53.536 --> 00:15:55.370
in police training videos?

417
00:15:55.371 --> 00:15:56.621
Based on what
we could piece together.

418
00:15:56.622 --> 00:15:58.915
he believed he had stumbled
upon a conspiracy...

419
00:15:58.916 --> 00:16:01.251
a series of connected murders
committed by person

420
00:16:01.252 --> 00:16:02.878
or persons unknown.

421
00:16:02.879 --> 00:16:04.671
If that were the case.
why not just report

422
00:16:04.672 --> 00:16:07.048
his suspicion?
He was a cop for 30 years.

423
00:16:07.049 --> 00:16:09.551
Well. Rich had
a bit of a reputation

424
00:16:09.552 --> 00:16:14.097
within the department for.
shall we say. magical thinking.

425
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:17.934
So unfortunately. his theory
was dismissed out of hand.

426
00:16:17.935 --> 00:16:19.895
But why did he think
the murders were connected?

427
00:16:19.896 --> 00:16:21.396
Well. for starters.
they were all stabbed

428
00:16:21.397 --> 00:16:23.523
in the chest.
but more importantly.

429
00:16:23.524 --> 00:16:25.150
each victim was found
with a penny

430
00:16:25.151 --> 00:16:26.610
either in or on their person.

431
00:16:26.611 --> 00:16:27.944
What do you mean "in"?

432
00:16:27.945 --> 00:16:30.071
One had a penny in her stomach.

433
00:16:30.072 --> 00:16:32.240
Another had one
shoved up his nose.

434
00:16:32.241 --> 00:16:33.575
Stella Brown lucked out.

435
00:16:33.576 --> 00:16:35.493
Hers was just
clasped in her hand.

436
00:16:35.494 --> 00:16:37.996
And when we re-examined
Marcus Ford's corpse.

437
00:16:37.997 --> 00:16:41.374
the ME found one inserted into
the heel of his left foot.

438
00:16:41.375 --> 00:16:43.084
Why?

439
00:16:43.085 --> 00:16:45.378
Did we mention that
they were all minted in 1930?

440
00:16:45.379 --> 00:16:47.631
- OK.
Well. I just got goosebumps.

441
00:16:47.632 --> 00:16:49.841
Rich's autopsy also revealed
that he had swallowed

442
00:16:49.842 --> 00:16:51.968
close to 50 pennies
before he died.

443
00:16:51.969 --> 00:16:53.220
Gross.

444
00:16:53.221 --> 00:16:54.930
So at this point.
was your theory...

445
00:16:54.931 --> 00:16:56.806
I actually have no idea what
their theory would have been.

446
00:16:56.807 --> 00:16:59.476
Yeah. well. I would tell you.
but we were way off the mark.

447
00:16:59.477 --> 00:17:01.686
which we were about to discover

448
00:17:01.687 --> 00:17:04.481
when we got access
to his cloud account.

449
00:17:04.482 --> 00:17:07.107
OK.

450
00:17:07.108 --> 00:17:09.693
I may have finally found it.

451
00:17:09.694 --> 00:17:12.447
I am so close to getting
some real answers.

452
00:17:14.659 --> 00:17:16.786
See that?

453
00:17:30.591 --> 00:17:33.093
Oh. whoa.

454
00:17:33.094 --> 00:17:34.094
Ha!

455
00:17:36.097 --> 00:17:38.139
Oh. my God.
No! No.

456
00:17:40.685 --> 00:17:43.103
<i>For a guy pretending to be dead.</i>

457
00:17:43.104 --> 00:17:44.980
breaking into a secure
military facility

458
00:17:44.981 --> 00:17:47.023
doesn't seem like the best idea.

459
00:17:47.024 --> 00:17:50.694
Well. he wasn't just breaking
into any military facility.

460
00:17:50.695 --> 00:17:52.153
It was Area 67.

461
00:17:52.154 --> 00:17:53.446
What does that mean?

462
00:17:53.447 --> 00:17:56.157
That's where the government
keeps the aliens.

463
00:18:04.417 --> 00:18:05.292
So Rich broke into
a secret government base

464
00:18:05.293 --> 00:18:07.168
on the hunt for
a massive conspiracy.

465
00:18:07.169 --> 00:18:08.670
then stabbed himself
in the chest?

466
00:18:08.671 --> 00:18:10.255
I mean. at that point.
it's obvious what happened.

467
00:18:10.256 --> 00:18:12.173
- Is it?
- Come on.

468
00:18:12.174 --> 00:18:14.259
Remember what Rich said
right before he died?

469
00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:15.844
I can't die.

470
00:18:15.845 --> 00:18:16.803
It's inside of me.

471
00:18:16.804 --> 00:18:18.555
It won't let me die.

472
00:18:18.556 --> 00:18:19.973
Yeah. I'm not following.

473
00:18:19.974 --> 00:18:22.726
Rich was exposed
to an alien parasite.

474
00:18:22.727 --> 00:18:25.270
It was inside him.

475
00:18:25.271 --> 00:18:27.814
Were you familiar with Area 67?

476
00:18:27.815 --> 00:18:29.607
- I'd heard of it.
Yeah.

477
00:18:29.608 --> 00:18:32.319
There's this AM radio station
I used to listen to

478
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:33.945
back in Foxburg.

479
00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:35.572
Kept me awake when
I was working late.

480
00:18:35.573 --> 00:18:38.408
The host was obsessed with UFOs.

481
00:18:38.409 --> 00:18:40.619
- "Val's Velvet Bunker"?
- That's the one.

482
00:18:40.620 --> 00:18:43.913
He was a little bit out there.
but always entertaining.

483
00:18:43.914 --> 00:18:47.292
<i>Area 51 is theater.</i>

484
00:18:47.293 --> 00:18:49.002
<i>Do you believe?</i>

485
00:18:49.003 --> 00:18:51.838
<i>Do you really believe
the most secretive</i>

486
00:18:51.839 --> 00:18:54.466
<i>military installation
in the world would let itself</i>

487
00:18:54.467 --> 00:18:56.468
<i>become a tourist attraction?</i>

488
00:18:56.469 --> 00:18:57.761
<i>No. no. no. no.</i>

489
00:18:57.762 --> 00:19:00.430
<i>Area 51 is the distraction.</i>

490
00:19:00.431 --> 00:19:03.391
<i>Area 67 is the real deal.</i>

491
00:19:03.392 --> 00:19:05.935
<i>You know why California
has all those earthquakes?</i>

492
00:19:05.936 --> 00:19:08.688
<i>It's not the San Andreas
Fault. my friends.</i>

493
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:11.858
<i>It's the sonic resonance
from Area 67's</i>

494
00:19:11.859 --> 00:19:13.693
<i>underground testing chambers.</i>

495
00:19:13.694 --> 00:19:15.612
Did you believe in his theories?

496
00:19:15.613 --> 00:19:17.030
No. no.

497
00:19:17.031 --> 00:19:18.823
Like I said. just entertainment.

498
00:19:18.824 --> 00:19:19.783
<i>Let's hear from a caller.</i>

499
00:19:19.784 --> 00:19:21.534
<i>Hi. name's John.</i>

500
00:19:21.535 --> 00:19:22.702
<i>Longtime listener.
fourth-time caller.</i>

501
00:19:22.703 --> 00:19:25.372
<i>- Hey. John from Foxburg.
Welcome back.</i>

502
00:19:25.373 --> 00:19:26.498
<i>What have you got
for us tonight?</i>

503
00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:29.085
<i>I swear to God I just saw a UFO.</i>

504
00:19:31.379 --> 00:19:34.464
John is such a common name.

505
00:19:34.465 --> 00:19:37.092
I'm open to the possibility
of extraterrestrial life.

506
00:19:37.093 --> 00:19:38.385
- You are?
- Yeah.

507
00:19:38.386 --> 00:19:40.011
I mean. it's a big universe.

508
00:19:40.012 --> 00:19:42.055
Anything could be out there.
- I don't know.

509
00:19:42.056 --> 00:19:44.891
People who claim to have seen
aliens tend to be a little off.

510
00:19:44.892 --> 00:19:46.684
You were friends
with a corpse. right?

511
00:19:46.685 --> 00:19:48.061
Well. yeah.
we were more than friends.

512
00:19:48.062 --> 00:19:49.688
but fair enough.
OK.

513
00:19:49.689 --> 00:19:52.107
Legally. is it necrophilia

514
00:19:52.108 --> 00:19:53.691
if she only did
over the clothes stuff?

515
00:19:53.692 --> 00:19:56.194
- That's a great question.
- Oh. I definitely believe.

516
00:19:56.195 --> 00:19:57.987
In fact.

517
00:19:57.988 --> 00:20:00.240
I've been abducted by aliens.

518
00:20:00.241 --> 00:20:02.617
- Really?
- Multiple times.

519
00:20:02.618 --> 00:20:06.037
Apparently.
I'm a fascinating subject.

520
00:20:06.038 --> 00:20:09.249
I remember the last time
Smitty was "abducted."

521
00:20:09.250 --> 00:20:10.917
Turns out he partied
too hard in Vegas

522
00:20:10.918 --> 00:20:12.544
and woke up in Wisconsin.

523
00:20:12.545 --> 00:20:14.295
Missing time.

524
00:20:14.296 --> 00:20:17.257
one of the hallmarks
of alien abductions.

525
00:20:17.258 --> 00:20:19.384
- And binge drinking.
- Point is.

526
00:20:19.385 --> 00:20:22.053
the government
had little gray men

527
00:20:22.054 --> 00:20:24.472
in their secret labs
for decades.

528
00:20:24.473 --> 00:20:26.266
What are they doing with them?

529
00:20:26.267 --> 00:20:28.893
They're implanting the aliens
in unsuspecting hosts

530
00:20:28.894 --> 00:20:30.520
and taking over their bodies.

531
00:20:30.521 --> 00:20:34.108
You just never know
who might be one of them.

532
00:20:35.735 --> 00:20:38.611
Some people in the station
believed Rich stabbed himself

533
00:20:38.612 --> 00:20:40.572
to kill an alien parasite.

534
00:20:40.573 --> 00:20:42.073
but I wouldn't say

535
00:20:42.074 --> 00:20:44.033
that was a dominant theory.

536
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:45.577
It wasn't long before
we figured out

537
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:48.037
Rich believed something darker.

538
00:20:48.038 --> 00:20:50.457
and it was connected
to the seven murders.

539
00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:52.083
Then why did Rich break
into the army base?

540
00:20:52.084 --> 00:20:54.711
Yes. I remember the incident.

541
00:20:54.712 --> 00:20:56.171
Rich Rowley cut through a fence.

542
00:20:56.172 --> 00:20:58.339
He trespassed on
government property.

543
00:20:58.340 --> 00:21:01.050
He was promptly apprehended
and sent on his way.

544
00:21:01.051 --> 00:21:03.595
Do you have any idea
what Rich was looking for?

545
00:21:03.596 --> 00:21:06.389
Uh. as it turns out.
he was looking for me.

546
00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:09.601
But not because of
any alleged aliens.

547
00:21:09.602 --> 00:21:12.020
So why did he come?

548
00:21:12.021 --> 00:21:14.981
Uh. this part is a...

549
00:21:14.982 --> 00:21:17.692
is a little bit embarrassing.
Um...

550
00:21:17.693 --> 00:21:19.986
before I found my calling
in the military.

551
00:21:19.987 --> 00:21:22.739
I thought that
I wanted to be an actor.

552
00:21:22.740 --> 00:21:25.700
and I was in a few DTV movies.

553
00:21:25.701 --> 00:21:26.826
<i>What's DTV?</i>

554
00:21:26.827 --> 00:21:27.952
You're so young.

555
00:21:27.953 --> 00:21:29.412
Uh. direct to video.

556
00:21:29.413 --> 00:21:31.748
They made all these
super cheap movies

557
00:21:31.749 --> 00:21:33.541
back in the '80s and '90s.

558
00:21:33.542 --> 00:21:35.084
<i>You make them as cheaply
as possible</i>

559
00:21:35.085 --> 00:21:37.128
<i>and then hope that someone
was drawn in enough</i>

560
00:21:37.129 --> 00:21:39.547
<i>by the cover art to rent them.</i>

561
00:21:39.548 --> 00:21:42.133
- A guy can't have a side gig?
- Totally.

562
00:21:42.134 --> 00:21:43.718
How did you get into acting?

563
00:21:43.719 --> 00:21:46.262
Some director scouted me
when I pulled him over.

564
00:21:46.263 --> 00:21:49.057
He said I had a bitchin' bod.

565
00:21:49.058 --> 00:21:50.725
<i>Well. he wasn't wrong.</i>

566
00:21:50.726 --> 00:21:53.603
But I gave it up 'cause
the people of this city

567
00:21:53.604 --> 00:21:55.688
needed a savior.
- Mm.

568
00:21:55.689 --> 00:21:57.941
Yeah. you are the model
of public service.

569
00:21:57.942 --> 00:21:59.776
Right.

570
00:21:59.777 --> 00:22:02.821
Anyway. Rich became
interested in this terrible

571
00:22:02.822 --> 00:22:06.032
B movie that I was in.
I played a monk.

572
00:22:06.033 --> 00:22:08.576
It was called
"300 Days of Hell."

573
00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:14.707
Terrible B movie.
that's what he called it?

574
00:22:14.708 --> 00:22:17.085
"300 Days of Hell" is the
scariest film of the 1990s.

575
00:22:17.086 --> 00:22:18.670
Really?

576
00:22:18.671 --> 00:22:20.630
"The Ring". "Scream."
"Blair Witch Project"?

577
00:22:20.631 --> 00:22:22.590
Which one of us executive
produced a horror movie?

578
00:22:22.591 --> 00:22:24.843
Trust me. "THDOH"

579
00:22:24.844 --> 00:22:26.845
is true nightmare fuel.

580
00:22:26.846 --> 00:22:28.930
It's not that scary.

581
00:22:28.931 --> 00:22:31.474
She made me watch it at the
beginning of our relationship.

582
00:22:31.475 --> 00:22:34.352
When he was still
trying to impress me.

583
00:22:34.353 --> 00:22:36.479
You wanna watch it
again tonight?

584
00:22:36.480 --> 00:22:39.232
- I would.
Totally.

585
00:22:39.233 --> 00:22:42.235
I do have plans. though.

586
00:22:42.236 --> 00:22:43.820
Yeah I'm not watching that crap.

587
00:22:43.821 --> 00:22:45.530
even if it is for a case.

588
00:22:45.531 --> 00:22:47.782
I see enough horror on the job.

589
00:22:47.783 --> 00:22:50.827
That being said.
"300 Days of Hell"

590
00:22:50.828 --> 00:22:52.829
was our first real window
into the rabbit hole

591
00:22:52.830 --> 00:22:54.247
that Rich had gone down.

592
00:22:54.248 --> 00:22:55.790
A rabbit hole filled
with demons...

593
00:22:55.791 --> 00:22:58.710
or rather. a demon.

594
00:22:58.711 --> 00:23:00.420
So Rich believed a demon
had killed all those people?

595
00:23:00.421 --> 00:23:02.130
No. the killers
were definitely human.

596
00:23:02.131 --> 00:23:03.923
- Killers. plural?
- Yeah.

597
00:23:03.924 --> 00:23:06.384
There was different trace DNA
on all the bodies.

598
00:23:06.385 --> 00:23:08.511
all from different subjects.
and none of them

599
00:23:08.512 --> 00:23:10.930
were in the system.
- Meaning?

600
00:23:10.931 --> 00:23:12.181
The murders were committed
by a group of people

601
00:23:12.182 --> 00:23:14.267
with shared beliefs.

602
00:23:14.268 --> 00:23:15.476
A murder cult?

603
00:23:15.477 --> 00:23:17.937
The cult believed a demon
named Malaphus

604
00:23:17.938 --> 00:23:20.273
had been possessing people
all across the city.

605
00:23:20.274 --> 00:23:24.235
jumping from host to host. and
it was up to them to stop it.

606
00:23:32.786 --> 00:23:34.871
The legend of Malaphus
is centuries old.

607
00:23:34.872 --> 00:23:38.082
The first mention we see of him
is 1433's

608
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:40.293
"Lesser Grimoire of Solomon"

609
00:23:40.294 --> 00:23:43.880
by Slovenian inquisitor
Terentius Bruma.

610
00:23:43.881 --> 00:23:48.009
a reference text of demons
and their attributes.

611
00:23:48.010 --> 00:23:50.136
- Gnarly.
- Right?

612
00:23:50.137 --> 00:23:53.139
He's also known as
the Deceiver. the Infestor.

613
00:23:53.140 --> 00:23:55.725
and Demon of 300 days.
Why?

614
00:23:55.726 --> 00:23:58.061
Once summoned to Earth.
Malaphus won't rest

615
00:23:58.062 --> 00:23:59.854
until he finds a human host.

616
00:23:59.855 --> 00:24:02.774
After possession begins.
he incubates

617
00:24:02.775 --> 00:24:04.984
300 days.

618
00:24:04.985 --> 00:24:06.527
What happens after 300 days?

619
00:24:06.528 --> 00:24:08.321
He reaches full strength.

620
00:24:08.322 --> 00:24:11.616
and his power
becomes uncontainable.

621
00:24:11.617 --> 00:24:12.993
Uh-oh.

622
00:24:14.370 --> 00:24:16.621
Um. if Malaphus
was summoned to Earth.

623
00:24:16.622 --> 00:24:18.247
how would one stop him?

624
00:24:18.248 --> 00:24:21.626
Bruma suggests killing the
host might slow Malaphus down.

625
00:24:21.627 --> 00:24:25.338
forcing him to regenerate
before he can find a new host.

626
00:24:25.339 --> 00:24:28.132
a process
that also can be slowed

627
00:24:28.133 --> 00:24:30.635
by the use of copper.

628
00:24:30.636 --> 00:24:33.304
- It was the pennies.
- The pennies.

629
00:24:33.305 --> 00:24:34.847
It all came back to the pennies.

630
00:24:34.848 --> 00:24:38.434
Before 1984.
U.S. pennies were 95% copper.

631
00:24:38.435 --> 00:24:40.979
So the copper in the pennies
was meant to bind the demon.

632
00:24:40.980 --> 00:24:42.313
but what about the 1930 part?

633
00:24:42.314 --> 00:24:45.150
Uh. are you familiar
with numerology?

634
00:24:46.694 --> 00:24:49.404
Some ancient peoples...
and Taylor Swift...

635
00:24:49.405 --> 00:24:52.407
believed there was
a mystical connection

636
00:24:52.408 --> 00:24:55.201
between letters and numbers.

637
00:24:55.202 --> 00:24:57.370
Using the Chaldean method.
the name Malaphus

638
00:24:57.371 --> 00:24:59.455
becomes a digit. 1930.

639
00:24:59.456 --> 00:25:01.999
- So you're saying...
- We had a theory.

640
00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:04.627
Whoever killed those people
believed the victims

641
00:25:04.628 --> 00:25:06.796
were possessed by Malaphus.

642
00:25:06.797 --> 00:25:10.550
They had to reach
Malaphus's host before

643
00:25:10.551 --> 00:25:12.260
he reached his true form.

644
00:25:12.261 --> 00:25:13.761
A 1930 penny was
the perfect tool.

645
00:25:13.762 --> 00:25:16.347
Yeah. Rich's talk of.
"it's inside me.

646
00:25:16.348 --> 00:25:18.683
it won't let me die."
he thought he was infested

647
00:25:18.684 --> 00:25:20.101
by this demon. too.

648
00:25:20.102 --> 00:25:21.644
and that's why
he killed himself.

649
00:25:21.645 --> 00:25:23.146
Wait.

650
00:25:23.147 --> 00:25:24.564
I thought Rich didn't
believe in Malaphus.

651
00:25:24.565 --> 00:25:26.858
Isn't that why he was
trying to stop the cult?

652
00:25:26.859 --> 00:25:29.110
Well. yes. but. I mean.
years of obsession and paranoia

653
00:25:29.111 --> 00:25:31.070
can do a number
on a person's psyche.

654
00:25:31.071 --> 00:25:32.196
I mean. it seems as though.
in the end.

655
00:25:32.197 --> 00:25:33.865
Rich could no longer distinguish

656
00:25:33.866 --> 00:25:35.491
fantasy from reality.

657
00:25:35.492 --> 00:25:37.243
And you got this theory
from Rich's files?

658
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:39.287
Well. I mean.
we actually got it from Lopez.

659
00:25:39.288 --> 00:25:41.873
And they say watching
old horror movies

660
00:25:41.874 --> 00:25:44.167
isn't a good use of time.

661
00:25:44.168 --> 00:25:46.419
I never said that.

662
00:25:53.635 --> 00:25:55.845
Are we safe. brother?

663
00:25:55.846 --> 00:25:57.847
Is Malaphus banished?

664
00:25:57.848 --> 00:25:59.599
His sigil is drawn.

665
00:25:59.600 --> 00:26:01.517
The rite is spoken.

666
00:26:01.518 --> 00:26:05.521
We have sealed his last
human vessel with copper.

667
00:26:11.945 --> 00:26:13.738
Heaven forgive us.

668
00:26:13.739 --> 00:26:15.698
Indeed.

669
00:26:15.699 --> 00:26:17.742
For hell will not.

670
00:26:18.911 --> 00:26:21.120
Midnight.

671
00:26:21.121 --> 00:26:24.165
the 300th day.

672
00:26:24.166 --> 00:26:26.793
Our task was done none too soon.

673
00:26:53.070 --> 00:26:55.114
<i>Yeah. that was me.</i>

674
00:26:57.491 --> 00:26:59.283
Do you guys want a glass?
- No. I'm good.

675
00:26:59.284 --> 00:27:01.786
Oh. you got anything stronger?

676
00:27:01.787 --> 00:27:04.330
Fine.
I'll just take a glass.

677
00:27:04.331 --> 00:27:06.374
OK. I'll. just...
I'll have nothing. actually.

678
00:27:06.375 --> 00:27:08.167
No fun for me.

679
00:27:08.168 --> 00:27:11.963
Yeah. that was
my first big movie role.

680
00:27:11.964 --> 00:27:15.633
Well. my only one. really.

681
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:18.511
Rich was so excited
when I told him I booked it.

682
00:27:18.512 --> 00:27:20.471
He helped me run lines.

683
00:27:20.472 --> 00:27:22.056
Did Rich buy in
to the Malaphus mythology?

684
00:27:22.057 --> 00:27:23.724
No.

685
00:27:23.725 --> 00:27:25.726
Weirdly. given all
the conspiracies that Rich

686
00:27:25.727 --> 00:27:28.896
believed in.
he was a total atheist.

687
00:27:28.897 --> 00:27:30.815
But I wouldn't have
blamed him after everything

688
00:27:30.816 --> 00:27:32.358
that happened on that shoot.

689
00:27:32.359 --> 00:27:34.069
Like what?

690
00:27:35.362 --> 00:27:37.280
Before production wrapped.

691
00:27:37.281 --> 00:27:39.282
the DP was paralyzed
driving to set.

692
00:27:39.283 --> 00:27:41.826
A stunt person had
his leg amputated.

693
00:27:41.827 --> 00:27:43.703
There were divorces. bankruptcies.

694
00:27:43.704 --> 00:27:45.246
Careers ended.

695
00:27:45.247 --> 00:27:49.292
One of the actors even died
in his hotel room.

696
00:27:49.293 --> 00:27:51.252
People say the production
was cursed.

697
00:27:51.253 --> 00:27:53.671
- What about you?
What do you believe?

698
00:27:53.672 --> 00:27:57.967
I believe the real curse
was the director.

699
00:27:57.968 --> 00:28:00.887
He was a reckless maniac that
didn't know how to run a set.

700
00:28:00.888 --> 00:28:03.472
- Cut.
Cut!

701
00:28:03.473 --> 00:28:05.850
Arthur! Arthur!

702
00:28:05.851 --> 00:28:09.729
Your strangulation.
it has to be real.

703
00:28:09.730 --> 00:28:11.898
I wanna feel the life
draining from him.

704
00:28:11.899 --> 00:28:15.610
You. you... you cannot move
from your position.

705
00:28:15.611 --> 00:28:17.320
Not even an inch.

706
00:28:17.321 --> 00:28:21.574
Guys. this ritual is
extremely specific.

707
00:28:21.575 --> 00:28:23.659
OK?
Let's go again.

708
00:28:23.660 --> 00:28:25.244
OK. I thought I was
choking you pretty well.

709
00:28:25.245 --> 00:28:26.704
I'm sorry.

710
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:27.538
OK. I'm gonna choke you
a little harder.

711
00:28:27.539 --> 00:28:29.332
Ready?

712
00:28:29.333 --> 00:28:31.334
Douglas was real touchy
about the religious stuff.

713
00:28:31.335 --> 00:28:33.628
I guess he had grown up
in some sort of commune.

714
00:28:33.629 --> 00:28:36.547
and this was all based on
stories he was told growing up.

715
00:28:36.548 --> 00:28:38.966
OK. but what I heard
is that they accidentally

716
00:28:38.967 --> 00:28:40.885
summoned Malaphus for real.

717
00:28:40.886 --> 00:28:42.595
The director found
some ancient tome

718
00:28:42.596 --> 00:28:45.973
and inserted the incantation
and rituals verbatim.

719
00:28:45.974 --> 00:28:47.350
Ooh. I love that.

720
00:28:47.351 --> 00:28:48.851
And that's what got me thinking

721
00:28:48.852 --> 00:28:50.561
about the penny killings.

722
00:28:50.562 --> 00:28:53.481
We found the first victim
just a little under 300 days

723
00:28:53.482 --> 00:28:55.524
after the summoning ritual
was filmed.

724
00:28:55.525 --> 00:28:57.818
We knew Rich was aware
of the Malaphus legends.

725
00:28:57.819 --> 00:28:59.737
It was only natural
to link them.

726
00:28:59.738 --> 00:29:01.864
So Rich thought the penny
victims were killed by people

727
00:29:01.865 --> 00:29:03.658
trying to stop Malaphus.

728
00:29:03.659 --> 00:29:05.952
Was he able to identify
any of these killers?

729
00:29:05.953 --> 00:29:07.162
We know he tried.

730
00:29:08.538 --> 00:29:10.206
- Hi.
- Hey. How are you?

731
00:29:10.207 --> 00:29:12.583
Jared.
- Hello. Wow.

732
00:29:12.584 --> 00:29:15.211
Um. it's a... it's a pleasure
to meet you. gentlemen.

733
00:29:15.212 --> 00:29:16.629
<i>Pleasure to meet you too.</i>

734
00:29:16.630 --> 00:29:18.130
Why don't you tell us
about yourselves?

735
00:29:18.131 --> 00:29:22.760
<i>Yeah. we. uh. co-starred
on a TV show together</i>

736
00:29:22.761 --> 00:29:25.137
for 15 seasons

737
00:29:25.138 --> 00:29:26.889
called "Supernatural."

738
00:29:26.890 --> 00:29:29.058
Yeah. we played Sam
and Dean Winchester.

739
00:29:29.059 --> 00:29:32.895
brothers that. you know.
tracked and fought

740
00:29:32.896 --> 00:29:34.855
supernatural beings.

741
00:29:34.856 --> 00:29:36.524
- Like "K-Pop Demon Hunters."
<i>- No.</i>

742
00:29:36.525 --> 00:29:37.817
<i>No. not like that.</i>

743
00:29:37.818 --> 00:29:39.652
<i>I mean. kind of like that.</i>

744
00:29:39.653 --> 00:29:40.861
<i>- No.
- Yeah.</i>

745
00:29:40.862 --> 00:29:43.197
OK. can you tell us
about your encounter

746
00:29:43.198 --> 00:29:44.991
with Rich Rowley?
- Yeah. yeah. yeah.

747
00:29:44.992 --> 00:29:46.701
Rich Rowley.

748
00:29:46.702 --> 00:29:51.372
He came to a fan event we did
last year at MonsterCon.

749
00:29:51.373 --> 00:29:52.832
Yeah. you know.
most people show up.

750
00:29:52.833 --> 00:29:57.044
and they just want
an autograph or a photo.

751
00:29:57.045 --> 00:30:00.631
But Rich was a bit of
a different beast altogether.

752
00:30:00.632 --> 00:30:02.842
Yeah. yeah.
he was... he was super

753
00:30:02.843 --> 00:30:05.011
fixated on this one
particular episode

754
00:30:05.012 --> 00:30:07.388
where we fought a demon.
- Malaphus.

755
00:30:07.389 --> 00:30:09.557
<i>Yeah. uh. that one.</i>

756
00:30:09.558 --> 00:30:14.103
Anyway he seemed to think
we. like. knew more

757
00:30:14.104 --> 00:30:15.938
about it than we were saying.

758
00:30:15.939 --> 00:30:16.689
More about what?

759
00:30:16.690 --> 00:30:18.566
Demon hunting.

760
00:30:18.567 --> 00:30:21.652
He kept. like. asking these
super pointed questions.

761
00:30:21.653 --> 00:30:23.863
like... like he was.
I don't know.

762
00:30:23.864 --> 00:30:25.031
testing us or something.

763
00:30:25.032 --> 00:30:27.241
- Did you have an answer?
- No.

764
00:30:27.242 --> 00:30:28.534
No. I mean. we didn't...

765
00:30:28.535 --> 00:30:30.161
we didn't come up
with these stories.

766
00:30:30.162 --> 00:30:31.829
You know. we just did
what the writers wrote.

767
00:30:31.830 --> 00:30:33.372
It's called acting.

768
00:30:33.373 --> 00:30:35.583
<i>There's no actual
demon hunters in real life.</i>

769
00:30:35.584 --> 00:30:36.751
<i>Exactly.</i>

770
00:30:36.752 --> 00:30:38.669
Uh. that's not exactly true.

771
00:30:38.670 --> 00:30:40.838
There is at least one.

772
00:30:40.839 --> 00:30:44.675
And it actually connected
to the movie.

773
00:30:44.676 --> 00:30:46.635
<i>We heard the director
brought a priest named</i>

774
00:30:46.636 --> 00:30:48.679
Father Simon McCabe
to bless the set

775
00:30:48.680 --> 00:30:50.014
every day before filming.

776
00:30:50.015 --> 00:30:51.640
Well. it was either that
or the whole crew

777
00:30:51.641 --> 00:30:53.225
was going to walk.

778
00:30:53.226 --> 00:30:56.354
Does that name
mean anything to you?

779
00:30:56.355 --> 00:30:57.772
About 15 years ago.

780
00:30:57.773 --> 00:31:00.232
Lopez and I had just finished
our rookie years.

781
00:31:00.233 --> 00:31:02.568
We responded to a call
at a house.

782
00:31:02.569 --> 00:31:05.112
Priest doing an exorcism
with a 16-year-old girl.

783
00:31:05.113 --> 00:31:06.238
Had been going on
for three days.

784
00:31:06.239 --> 00:31:09.075
Father. no.

785
00:31:09.076 --> 00:31:11.827
Police!

786
00:31:11.828 --> 00:31:13.454
Help her!

787
00:31:13.455 --> 00:31:15.664
Please!

788
00:31:21.088 --> 00:31:24.465
Get away from her!

789
00:31:24.466 --> 00:31:28.219
Father. forgive me.

790
00:31:36.561 --> 00:31:37.728
Did you feel like
you'd seen the devil?

791
00:31:37.729 --> 00:31:38.938
The only thing in that room
that belonged in hell

792
00:31:38.939 --> 00:31:42.108
was Father Simon.
- He kept saying he had to.

793
00:31:42.109 --> 00:31:44.443
The whole way to the station.
"I'm sorry. I had to.

794
00:31:44.444 --> 00:31:45.945
I'm sorry. I had to."

795
00:31:45.946 --> 00:31:47.822
Because he believed
she was possessed?

796
00:31:47.823 --> 00:31:49.323
She had a brain tumor.

797
00:31:49.324 --> 00:31:51.867
That's what they found
after the autopsy.

798
00:31:51.868 --> 00:31:53.911
She needed a doctor.
not an exorcism.

799
00:31:53.912 --> 00:31:56.413
And he wasn't a man of God.
He was a killer.

800
00:31:56.414 --> 00:31:58.124
The courts agreed.

801
00:31:58.125 --> 00:32:01.043
So Father Simon was convicted
of first-degree murder.

802
00:32:01.044 --> 00:32:03.504
When we processed him.
we found a penny in his pocket.

803
00:32:03.505 --> 00:32:05.089
Nothing else. just a penny.

804
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:06.423
It didn't mean anything
at the time.

805
00:32:06.424 --> 00:32:08.467
but after Rich connected
those seven murders.

806
00:32:08.468 --> 00:32:10.386
it seemed likely
he was involved.

807
00:32:10.387 --> 00:32:12.304
Involved like. he killed them?

808
00:32:12.305 --> 00:32:14.807
No. Simon was already
in prison when five

809
00:32:14.808 --> 00:32:17.268
of the murders took place.
and his DNA didn't match

810
00:32:17.269 --> 00:32:19.311
any that was found
on the corpses.

811
00:32:19.312 --> 00:32:21.480
But he could have been part
of whatever group

812
00:32:21.481 --> 00:32:23.357
Rich was so afraid of.

813
00:32:23.358 --> 00:32:25.609
Which means he knew more
than he had told us.

814
00:32:25.610 --> 00:32:27.987
So we had to go back.

815
00:32:27.988 --> 00:32:30.781
Officers. I remember you.

816
00:32:30.782 --> 00:32:32.616
You... you were the ones
who tried to stop the ritual.

817
00:32:32.617 --> 00:32:34.368
Just wish we would
have gotten here sooner.

818
00:32:34.369 --> 00:32:35.911
Becca Scott
might still be alive.

819
00:32:35.912 --> 00:32:38.372
Oh. she was long gone
before you arrived.

820
00:32:38.373 --> 00:32:40.791
The demon saw to that.
- Malaphus?

821
00:32:40.792 --> 00:32:42.376
Shh.

822
00:32:42.377 --> 00:32:44.670
Do not say its name
in my presence.

823
00:32:44.671 --> 00:32:47.590
What. are you afraid we
might accidentally summon it?

824
00:32:47.591 --> 00:32:50.301
You may scorn me and my beliefs.

825
00:32:50.302 --> 00:32:52.178
but I have fought this evil.

826
00:32:52.179 --> 00:32:54.346
I know enough to fear its power.

827
00:32:54.347 --> 00:32:56.891
What's more evil
than murdering a child?

828
00:32:56.892 --> 00:32:59.351
I took no pleasure in the act.

829
00:32:59.352 --> 00:33:01.061
I'm grateful I had the courage
to do what was necessary.

830
00:33:01.062 --> 00:33:02.646
Courage?

831
00:33:02.647 --> 00:33:05.232
Tell us about the penny
that was in your pocket.

832
00:33:05.233 --> 00:33:07.234
In the movie "300 Days of Hell".

833
00:33:07.235 --> 00:33:09.320
Malaphus is sealed inside
his host with copper

834
00:33:09.321 --> 00:33:11.030
before he can be killed...

835
00:33:11.031 --> 00:33:13.115
Uh. banished. not killed.

836
00:33:13.116 --> 00:33:14.867
What's the difference?

837
00:33:14.868 --> 00:33:18.037
The demon is a parasite.

838
00:33:18.038 --> 00:33:19.580
It needs a host.

839
00:33:19.581 --> 00:33:21.373
Once you kill the body
that inhabits it.

840
00:33:21.374 --> 00:33:23.209
it'll find a new one.

841
00:33:23.210 --> 00:33:27.046
Becca Scott was just a single
battle in a larger war.

842
00:33:27.047 --> 00:33:31.383
If you're in here.
who's doing the fighting now?

843
00:33:31.384 --> 00:33:33.677
The Knights of Avila.

844
00:33:33.678 --> 00:33:35.679
Los Angeles has a long history

845
00:33:35.680 --> 00:33:38.265
of spiritualism.
esoteric religions

846
00:33:38.266 --> 00:33:39.850
that go back over 100 years.

847
00:33:39.851 --> 00:33:42.728
So think Aleister Crowley.
Jack Parsons.

848
00:33:42.729 --> 00:33:44.730
L. Ron Hubbard.
- He freaking loves this stuff.

849
00:33:44.731 --> 00:33:46.315
I do.

850
00:33:46.316 --> 00:33:48.275
Anyway. a lot of these groups
started out

851
00:33:48.276 --> 00:33:50.986
as fraternal orders.
similar to the Freemasons.

852
00:33:50.987 --> 00:33:52.947
where people would gather
and... and... share...

853
00:33:52.948 --> 00:33:54.240
- Men.
- Well. yeah.

854
00:33:54.241 --> 00:33:56.700
Yes. and...
and some women.

855
00:33:56.701 --> 00:33:59.828
And they would share new ideas.
explore philosophies.

856
00:33:59.829 --> 00:34:02.915
They also liked partying.
doing drugs.

857
00:34:02.916 --> 00:34:05.501
and performing
weird sex rituals.

858
00:34:05.502 --> 00:34:08.128
Sign me up.

859
00:34:08.129 --> 00:34:11.506
For the intellectual exchanging
of ideas. obviously.

860
00:34:11.507 --> 00:34:12.925
So the Knights of Avila
is one of these groups?

861
00:34:12.926 --> 00:34:14.677
It was.

862
00:34:14.678 --> 00:34:16.303
Like a lot of the similar
organizations at the time.

863
00:34:16.304 --> 00:34:17.846
it fell apart
when the founder died.

864
00:34:17.847 --> 00:34:18.930
It hasn't been active in...

865
00:34:18.931 --> 00:34:20.640
60 years?

866
00:34:20.641 --> 00:34:22.560
Then what was
Father Simon talking about?

867
00:34:22.561 --> 00:34:25.562
Based on Tim and Lopez's
conversation with Father Simon.

868
00:34:25.563 --> 00:34:27.398
we began to believe
that the group.

869
00:34:27.399 --> 00:34:29.858
or at least the name.

870
00:34:29.859 --> 00:34:32.361
had been revived
sometime in the late '90s

871
00:34:32.362 --> 00:34:35.238
to the early 2000s
and re-branded

872
00:34:35.239 --> 00:34:38.158
as some kind of
demon hunting cult.

873
00:34:38.159 --> 00:34:40.494
So Rich was actually right.

874
00:34:40.495 --> 00:34:42.663
There was a murderous cabal
after him.

875
00:34:42.664 --> 00:34:43.955
It seemed that way.

876
00:34:43.956 --> 00:34:46.082
and we were getting close

877
00:34:46.083 --> 00:34:48.294
to discovering
who their ringleader was.

878
00:34:48.295 --> 00:34:51.213
I found him.

879
00:34:51.214 --> 00:34:53.465
- Found who?
- Doug Roberts.

880
00:34:53.466 --> 00:34:55.509
I wanna feel
the life draining from him!

881
00:34:55.510 --> 00:34:57.136
Oh. you mean the director
of the sad little demon porn?

882
00:34:57.137 --> 00:34:58.512
Where?

883
00:34:58.513 --> 00:35:00.097
I was going through
some old industry trades

884
00:35:00.098 --> 00:35:02.641
from around the time "THDOH"
was slated to come out.

885
00:35:02.642 --> 00:35:04.852
One of the articles
mentioned that Roberts

886
00:35:04.853 --> 00:35:06.020
was a client
of Stewart Winecliff

887
00:35:06.021 --> 00:35:07.646
at the Golden Talent Agency.

888
00:35:07.647 --> 00:35:09.273
The guy hasn't made
a movie in 26 years.

889
00:35:09.274 --> 00:35:10.566
I doubt they still rep him.

890
00:35:10.567 --> 00:35:12.526
Not actively. no.

891
00:35:12.527 --> 00:35:14.403
But I called their offices.
and I bribed...

892
00:35:14.404 --> 00:35:16.572
or like. I talked one of
the assistants into giving me

893
00:35:16.573 --> 00:35:18.282
the address where
his residual checks are sent.

894
00:35:18.283 --> 00:35:19.867
It's downtown.
Let's go.

895
00:35:19.868 --> 00:35:21.577
Uh. hold on.

896
00:35:21.578 --> 00:35:23.037
You just wanna go
doorstep the guy?

897
00:35:23.038 --> 00:35:24.288
If that means go knock on a door

898
00:35:24.289 --> 00:35:25.914
while also filming. then yes.

899
00:35:25.915 --> 00:35:28.125
Yeah. I'm not in the business
of gotcha journalism.

900
00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:31.211
What about the business
of making that paper?

901
00:35:31.212 --> 00:35:32.713
The guap?

902
00:35:32.714 --> 00:35:34.590
Money. guy.

903
00:35:34.591 --> 00:35:36.842
Come on. the doc business
is over-saturated these days.

904
00:35:36.843 --> 00:35:39.386
We need footage that P-O-Ps.

905
00:35:39.387 --> 00:35:40.846
and what pops more
than blindsiding

906
00:35:40.847 --> 00:35:43.349
a potential cult leader?

907
00:35:43.350 --> 00:35:44.391
Come on.

908
00:35:44.392 --> 00:35:46.018
What's the worst
that could happen?

909
00:35:47.562 --> 00:35:50.189
This is it.
- OK.

910
00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:52.024
- Um. here.
Here's your camera.

911
00:35:52.025 --> 00:35:53.901
Um. I don't operate.

912
00:35:53.902 --> 00:35:54.985
Oh. well.

913
00:35:57.781 --> 00:36:01.325
Now. you do.

914
00:36:01.326 --> 00:36:03.619
Let's go.

915
00:36:03.620 --> 00:36:06.205
- What floor is it on?
- Eight.

916
00:36:06.206 --> 00:36:08.624
But there's an elevator.
Don't worry.

917
00:36:14.506 --> 00:36:17.675
- Are you sure it's that way?
- Yep.

918
00:36:17.676 --> 00:36:19.301
Nope.

919
00:36:19.302 --> 00:36:22.721
You know. at the risk of
being called a scaredy cat.

920
00:36:22.722 --> 00:36:24.723
you do understand
that this is inherently

921
00:36:24.724 --> 00:36:27.267
neither a wise
nor safe activity?

922
00:36:27.268 --> 00:36:29.478
You're asking a woman
if she understands

923
00:36:29.479 --> 00:36:33.107
that it's inherently dangerous
to go anywhere or do anything?

924
00:36:33.108 --> 00:36:35.984
When you put it that way.
I sound like an ass.

925
00:36:35.985 --> 00:36:37.069
Yeah.

926
00:36:39.697 --> 00:36:41.240
Maybe we should come back?

927
00:36:41.241 --> 00:36:43.659
Hey. Hello.

928
00:36:43.660 --> 00:36:45.411
Douglas Roberts.
we're here to question you

929
00:36:45.412 --> 00:36:47.621
about murders and demons.

930
00:36:47.622 --> 00:36:49.873
That should get his attention.

931
00:36:49.874 --> 00:36:51.500
Oh.

932
00:36:51.501 --> 00:36:53.878
I am just an intern.

933
00:36:58.758 --> 00:37:02.344
So clearly we're not
deceased. which means...

934
00:37:02.345 --> 00:37:03.929
We saved you from certain death.

935
00:37:03.930 --> 00:37:05.347
I'm not sure
how certain it was. right?

936
00:37:05.348 --> 00:37:06.974
Oh. it felt
pretty certain to me.

937
00:37:06.975 --> 00:37:08.392
Please don't kill us.

938
00:37:08.393 --> 00:37:09.893
We will join your cult.
Is there a membership fee

939
00:37:09.894 --> 00:37:11.520
or a secret handshake?

940
00:37:11.521 --> 00:37:12.771
I love a secret handshake.
- Ignore her.

941
00:37:12.772 --> 00:37:14.273
She's not right in the head.

942
00:37:14.274 --> 00:37:16.066
In fact. she has
short-term memory issues.

943
00:37:16.067 --> 00:37:17.860
So if you let her go now.
she won't remember any of this.

944
00:37:17.861 --> 00:37:19.653
- Just shut up.
No one's going anywhere.

945
00:37:19.654 --> 00:37:20.904
I mean. technically.
we're all going somewhere.

946
00:37:25.493 --> 00:37:27.911
- All right. let them go.
Put your hands up.

947
00:37:27.912 --> 00:37:31.540
Up against the Jeep. now.
Let's go.

948
00:37:36.337 --> 00:37:38.589
Oh. hey.

949
00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:41.175
Thanks for trying to save me.
even though

950
00:37:41.176 --> 00:37:42.968
I'm the one
who put us in danger.

951
00:37:42.969 --> 00:37:44.678
No problem.

952
00:37:44.679 --> 00:37:46.680
I was about to do
the same thing. but you just

953
00:37:46.681 --> 00:37:48.223
beat me to it.

954
00:37:48.224 --> 00:37:50.434
I can be noble. too.
- No doubt.

955
00:37:50.435 --> 00:37:52.644
Uh. I get very claustrophobic.

956
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:54.730
Can I just point out how
claustrophobic I get. please?

957
00:37:54.731 --> 00:37:57.149
So when did you
and Douglas meet?

958
00:37:57.150 --> 00:37:58.484
In the movie.

959
00:37:58.485 --> 00:38:02.237
He was. you know.
so commanding and driven

960
00:38:02.238 --> 00:38:04.114
and everything I wasn't.

961
00:38:04.115 --> 00:38:06.283
When did he start talking
about killing the demon?

962
00:38:06.284 --> 00:38:08.577
It was. uh. at least
a year after that.

963
00:38:08.578 --> 00:38:11.246
He would call me late at night

964
00:38:11.247 --> 00:38:13.332
and talk about the demon
and how scared

965
00:38:13.333 --> 00:38:14.875
he was for the world.

966
00:38:14.876 --> 00:38:17.503
and eventually
it started to make sense.

967
00:38:17.504 --> 00:38:20.672
And he told you that
someone was possessed?

968
00:38:20.673 --> 00:38:22.633
- Correct.
Her name was Cynthia.

969
00:38:22.634 --> 00:38:24.301
Um.

970
00:38:24.302 --> 00:38:27.179
she cried when I tied her up.
and she kept saying

971
00:38:27.180 --> 00:38:29.598
that she was not a demon.

972
00:38:29.599 --> 00:38:31.392
She begged me
to believe her. and...

973
00:38:35.605 --> 00:38:38.816
At that point.
he was very deep in my head.

974
00:38:38.817 --> 00:38:41.235
And then tonight.
you know. all the lies

975
00:38:41.236 --> 00:38:43.403
he was spewing at the end.

976
00:38:43.404 --> 00:38:45.239
it was like somebody
turned on a light switch.

977
00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:47.866
I could just see him
for who he was.

978
00:38:47.867 --> 00:38:49.452
So pathetic.

979
00:38:52.455 --> 00:38:54.999
We'll need you to write up
a detailed confession.

980
00:38:59.712 --> 00:39:01.464
I would like to make a deal.

981
00:39:03.174 --> 00:39:05.759
Uh. we have already located
your co-conspirators.

982
00:39:05.760 --> 00:39:08.929
You don't really have
anything to offer.

983
00:39:08.930 --> 00:39:12.057
You don't want to know what
an alien spaceship looks like?

984
00:39:13.726 --> 00:39:17.479
I am all that stands between
the world

985
00:39:17.480 --> 00:39:19.064
and damnation.

986
00:39:19.065 --> 00:39:20.941
So all of the people
that you had targeted.

987
00:39:20.942 --> 00:39:24.736
they had to die
for the greater good?

988
00:39:24.737 --> 00:39:28.490
Yes. and my heart breaks
for each of them.

989
00:39:28.491 --> 00:39:31.535
But I will not let innocents
fall to perdition.

990
00:39:31.536 --> 00:39:33.662
OK. have you had
your fill of BS?

991
00:39:33.663 --> 00:39:34.830
God. yes.

992
00:39:34.831 --> 00:39:35.914
OK. me. too.

993
00:39:35.915 --> 00:39:40.294
So. uh. first victim.
Cynthia Green.

994
00:39:40.295 --> 00:39:42.546
You dated for two years
before she cheated on you.

995
00:39:42.547 --> 00:39:45.507
Marcus Ford. he worked as
a teamster on your movie.

996
00:39:45.508 --> 00:39:48.302
then later sued you
for nonpayment.

997
00:39:48.303 --> 00:39:52.556
Pamela Jones wrote a scathing
review of your movie.

998
00:39:52.557 --> 00:39:53.724
Really? I...

999
00:39:53.725 --> 00:39:55.809
I had no idea.

1000
00:39:55.810 --> 00:39:59.187
All seven victims were people
who wronged you in some way.

1001
00:39:59.188 --> 00:40:01.064
You don't even believe
in the demon.

1002
00:40:01.065 --> 00:40:03.108
You just used it as a tool
to get people with weak minds

1003
00:40:03.109 --> 00:40:04.986
to do your dirty work for you.

1004
00:40:07.113 --> 00:40:08.906
Exactly.

1005
00:40:08.907 --> 00:40:10.532
I was the director.

1006
00:40:10.533 --> 00:40:12.826
I think you'll find
I never laid a finger

1007
00:40:12.827 --> 00:40:14.661
on any of the victims.

1008
00:40:14.662 --> 00:40:18.123
And I think you will find
that Manson died in prison.

1009
